pull.title: Remove unused CDiskBlockPos* argument from ProcessNewBlock
pull.body: Based on #9014 because I'm too lazy to rebase conflicting PRs everywhere, but realized the CDiskBlockPos* argument to ProcessNewBlock is entirely unused.

events.message: Remove unused CDiskBlockPos* argument from ProcessNewBlock

events.body:
Nice catch, this has been unused since #7917 made reindex stop using `ProcessNewBlock`.

utACK a13fa4c80f792ffba8a77737754506aa849929af, but I wished github would stop showing commits that were merged elsewhere.

utACK a13fa4c
<sub>GitHub only resorts the commits after a force push. You'd have to push an empty commit and then force push it away. `git checkout branchName && git commit --allow-empty && git push origin branchName && git reset --hard HEAD~ && git push origin branchName -f`
@MarcoFalke oh thats a cool trick, didnt know that worked...anyway, did so.
